title: Jefferson Parish President John Young hopes to follow Dardenne in lieutenant governor race
text:
Jefferson Parish President John Young hopes to follow Dardenne in lieutenant governor race Published 6:36 PM CDT Oct 24, 2015 A Large Text Photos 
Jefferson Parish President John Young has set up his campaign watch party Saturday night at Basin Street Station in New Orleans. Related Coast Guard rescues fisherman... 
It’s already been a long day for the first-time lieutenant governor candidate. He cast his ballot at 7 a.m. and then attended campaign events and met with volunteers. 
Young took a break from last-minute campaigning Saturday afternoon to cheer on his son, who had a high school football game. 
WDSU-TV and WDSU.com will be reporting results throughout election night from Basin Street, while keeping a close eye on Orleans Parish. Typically, the parish votes Democrat, but back in 2011, during the last lieutenant governor race, Republican Jay Dardenne won Orleans Parish by less than 1 percent and went on to win the night. 
Young hopes to follow in his fellow Republican’s footsteps with a win Saturday night.
